{{More footnotes|date=February 2013}} {{coord|22.965284|S|43.237939|W|type:edu|display=title}} {{Infobox University | name = IMPA | image = IMPA Logo.png | image_size = 220px | established = 1952<ref>Francisco de Oliveira Castro. ''A Matemática no Brasil'', Editora da Unicamp, p. 74.</ref> | type = [[Public university|Public]] | head_label = Director | head = [[Marcelo Viana]] | city = [[Rio de Janeiro]] | country = [[Brazil]] | researchers = 32 | campus = [[Urban area|Urban]] | website = {{URL|http://www.impa.br/opencms/en/|impa.br (English)}} }} The '''Instituto National de Matemática Pura e Aplicada''' ('''IMPA'''; {{lang-en| National Institute for Pure and Applied Mathematics}}) is widely considered to be the foremost research and educational institution of [[Brazil]] in the area of [[mathematics]]. It is located in the city of [[Rio de Janeiro]], and was formerly known simply as ''Instituto de Matemática Pura e Aplicada'', hence its official abbreviation.
As of 2015, IMPA does research in [[algebra]], [[Mathematical analysis|analysis]], [[differential geometry]], [[partial differential equations]], [[computer graphics]], [[fluid dynamics]], [[holomorphic dynamics]], [[mathematical economics]], [[symplectic geometry]], [[algebraic geometry]], [[Mathematical optimization|optimization]], [[probability theory]], [[dynamical system]]s, and [[ergodic theory]]. It is aiming to expand its lines of research to include [[topology]], [[number theory]], [[combinatorics]], and [[discrete mathematics]] in general and its applications.<ref>[http://www.impa.br/opencms/pt/pesquisa/pesquisa_areas_de_pesquisa/index.html] {{dead link|date=October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://w3.impa.br/~viana/out/Panorama_Matematica.pdf|format=PDF|title=Matemática e Estatística do Tamanho do Brasil Papel da Sociedade Brasileira de Matemática|author=Marcelo Viana|website=W3.impa.gr|accessdate=19 October 2018}}</ref>
[[Artur Avila]], a 2014 [[Fields Medal]]ist, is a researcher at IMPA and received his Ph.D there.<ref>{{cite news |last=Romero |first=Simon |date=Aug 27, 2014 |title=From a Compound in the Brazilian Hills, Excellence in Math Emerges |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/08/28/world/americas/from-a-compound-in-the-brazilian-hills-excellence-in-math-emerges.html |newspaper=The New York Times |location= |publisher= |accessdate= }}</ref> Among its researchers also are [[Jacob Palis]], [[Elon Lages Lima]], [[Maurício Peixoto]], [[Manfredo do Carmo]], [[Marcelo Viana]], [[Welington de Melo]], [[Enrique Pujals]], [[Harold Rosenberg (mathematician)|Harold Rosenberg]], [[Marcos Dajczer]], [[Carlos Gustavo Moreira]], [[Fernando Codá Marques]], [[César Camacho]], [[Arnaldo Garcia]], [[Alfredo Noel Iusem]], [[Karl-Otto Stöhr]], [[Robert Morris (mathematician)|Robert Morris]], and [[Carolina Araujo (mathematician)|Carolina Araujo]].<ref>[http://www.impa.br/opencms/pt/pesquisa/pesquisa_pesquisadores/pesquisadores_do_impa.html] {{dead link|date=October 2018}}</ref>
